  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Data Element: LESION SIZE (PATHOLOGICAL) - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
    <p>
      <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_lesion_size__pathological_">LESION SIZE (PATHOLOGICAL)</xref>
 is the same as attribute 
              <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_lesion_size">LESION SIZE</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
      <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_lesion_size__pathological_">LESION SIZE (PATHOLOGICAL)</xref>
 is the diameter of the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_lesion">Lesion</xref>, (or largest 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_lesion">Lesion</xref>
 if there is more than one), where the histology of a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_sample">SAMPLE</xref>
 proves to be invasive, where the 
              <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_ucum_unit_of_measurement">UCUM UNIT OF MEASUREMENT</xref>
 is 
              <i>'Millimetres (mm)'</i>.        </p>
  </div>
